==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} ''[[neveu#Middle English|neveu, nepheu]]'' "nephew, grandson" from {{etyl|fro}} ''[[neveu#Old French|neveu]]'' "nephew, grandson" (Modern French ''[[neveu#French|neveu]]'' "nephew") from {{etyl|la}} ''[[nepotem|nepōtem]]'', accusative of ''[[nepos|nepōs]]'' "nephew, grandson" from {{proto|Indo-European|nepot-|grandchild, sister's son|lang=en}}. Akin to {{etyl|goh|-}} ''[[nevo#Old High German|nevo]]'' "nephew, grandson" ({{etyl|de|-}} ''[[Neffe#German|Neffe]]'' "nephew"). Displaced native [[Middle English]] ''[[neve#Middle English|neve, neave]]'' "nephew, grandson" (from [[Old English]] ''[[nefa#Old English|nefa]]'' "nephew, grandson").

